Documentation

Introduction

Downzilla is an online service for extracting downloadable media information from supported websites.

The service detects available media streams and presents supported download options.

---

How It Works

1. Paste a supported video URL.
2. Click Search.
3. Downzilla analyzes the video url.
4. Available formats are displayed.
5. Select your preferred format.
6. Click Download to begin download (might take some time to begin)

---

Features

- Fast media extraction
- Multiple video qualities
- Audio-only downloads
- Playlist support (where supported)
- Mobile-friendly interface
- video streaming
- sharing download link

---

Supported Formats

Formats depend on the source website and may include:

- MP4
- WebM
- MP3
- M4A

---

Error Messages

Invalid URL

The provided URL is not supported or is incorrectly formatted.

Video Unavailable

The content cannot currently be accessed.

Extraction Failed

The media could not be processed. Please try again later.

Rate Limited

Too many requests were received. Wait a few minutes before trying again.

---

Privacy

Downzilla does not permanently store downloaded media. Temporary processing may occur to generate download information.

